main event: A round, silver object was observed by military and civilian personnel near Elgin Air Force Base, Florida on November 15, 1956.
interesting points: The object was described as round and silver in color.
The object was moving at a high rate of speed.
The object was observed for approximately 30 minutes.
The sighting was reported by Lt. Colonel Richard H. Lane, Assistant G-2 of the Air Intelligence Division.
No photographs were included in the report.
location: Vicinity of Elgin Air Force Base, Florida
